	I would recommend this hotel as it offers good value for money with very friendly and helpful staff.	It was our first time to Dubai and we were uncertain where to stay as it is very spread out. After hours of research on the internet, we decided on the Jumeira Rotana. The hotel is in a very good location, the city taxis are cheap enough so you can get to all the places of interest quite easily. The Boston Bar was good fun, plenty of sport if you like that, but they also do a quiz there and have a DJ who will play any tunes you ask for. The price of food and drinks there are on a par with other hotels and the quality is good. The Boston Bar have a brunch on a Friday and that is always good value for money. The service in the hotel is very good, the staff are friendly and helpful. The rooms are spacious (we had a standard room and it was a good size for a weeks stay) and very clean. The hotel supply complimentary tea and coffee in your room and a small bottle of water every day. Mini bar is expensive, but there is a small supermarket around the back of the hotel where you can buy soft drinks and nibbles at reasonable prices. Our stay was room only and the hotel wanted 75 dirhams per person for breakfast so we found a couple of cafe's behind the hotel where we could get something cheaper. The Pilipino cafe has an american breakfast (you have to ask for it) at a reasonable price. There are many other cafe's so there is a bit of choice. The pool area wasn't brilliant, although the hotel do bring round fresh fruit kebabs (free of charge) which was lovely. The pool is clean but the sun bed cusions are a little grubby, but you get clean towels supplied so you can cover the cusions up. Overall we were very happy with our choice of hotel, we would recommend it and would stay there again. Dubai is a very expensive holiday destination and this hotel offers great value for money.	
