Mar 8 2008 	Fantastic Location but Poor Transfer Arrangements	The room was massive and they will allow you for an early check-in depending on occupancy. We arrived early and had early check-in by 10 a.m. Excellent!!Hotel staff were friendly, but poor arrangement for airport transfer company which the hotel has the contract with. When we asked hotel to arrange our airport pick-up for 4 adults and 2 children, they charged us per head. They told us to contact &quot;United Car Rental&quot; counter at the airport upon arrival, but the staff there provided us with a car (4 seats) and expected the 2 young children (ages 6&amp;7) to stand or kneeled down with the luggage with no seat belt. We asked them to provide the sufficient car which we expected a minibus or a van instead. We had to wait for half an hour outdoor at the multi-storey parking in front of the airport. The driver was very rude and we had to ask them to arrange a proper vehicle with enough seat belts for everybody. They said why we were so fussy and had a problem with these as the kids can stand or sit on the knees. We ended up had 2 cars. When we checked out the hotel still charged us for 2 cars which was more expensive than charging per head for this which was not our choice. We denied to pay for the second car. We also asked them to arrange for the transit visa (supposed to be free but you pay only for hotel handling service) and they also put double charges for that at the end. Be careful....trying to check all the hotel bills before you pay.Food was nice and got more variety for breakfast. Good location for lots of restaurants and local supermarket nearby....better than staying in hotels on Jumeira Beach which takes miles and miles to go anywhere and you can only eat inside the hotel. Heavy traffic during rush hour every where. We went to the restaurant in The Burj Al Arab Hotel (you need a booking prior to arrival). It was fantastic. Tourists cannot get into the hotel without bookings. Overall Dubai is ok... It's like you can tick in the box once you have been there...done that. And that's it...finished!! Not many things to do as much for family with young children, but it's a good experience and we don't regret we have been there.	
Feb 26 2008	Very Good functional hotel in a good location	Having used trip advisor many times to get a 'feel' for accomodation I feel somewhat compelled to contribute and write a review that may be helpful to others.Stayed at the Rotana in february 08, overall the experience was excellent helped by the extremely helpful and friendly staff. I would describe this hotel as business like, efficent, functional and does exactly what it says on the tin.There are two reasonable priced bars in the hotel and many great eateries may be found round the corner on the main street. The restaurant on the fith floor offered a good choice of well presented food at a resonable price. The room itself was quiet, spacious and clean though the bathroom grouting etc would benefit from abit of upgrading. The roof top pool was warm and water clarity was good, however the grouting and scum tide around the pool was personally a little off putting. The area itself is quiet and relaxing with very helpful and friendly pool attendants.Notwithstanding the almost irrelevant negative comments without cuncation I would not have the slightest reservation in recommending this hotel and would certainly stay there again.	
Feb 3 2008 	Good Hotel for Relaxing Break	Stayed here for 6 nights, rooms are spacious with comfortable beds. Bathroom was fine but could do with a little upgrade to bring it up to the standard of the rest of hotel. The Boston Bar has great food and excellent lively atmosphere in the evening. The staff could not do enough to make our stay enjoyable. The restaurant on the top floor offered a great choice of dishes for all meals. Each night had a different theme. The hotel is situated in an area where there is an excellent choice of other places to eat. Would advise travelling around in a taxi, they are very cheap. It was just too hot to walk about during the day. I would stay here again. Dubai is an excellent stopover location or if you want guaranteed sunshine to top up your tan.	
Dec 14 2007 	Good Location Nice Rooms	We stayed in this hotel for 3 nights on a transit through to Sri Lanka. The staff were extremely nice and helpful, the rooms were lovely (although the bathrooms were a bit dated), a decent buffet breakfast - everything you would expect from a 4* hotel. TIt wasn't far to the main attractions via taxis which are dirt cheap (the most you will probably pay is £5 for a 45 min taxi journey. There are also some lovely restaurants within walking distance. The only slight negatives are that there is a loud bar full of middle-aged, loud ex-pats downstairs where the food is not great and that the pool is quite small and very warm!! Not great for cooling off in the heat!We booked on asiarooms and got a good deal.	
Dec 2 2007	OK hotel	The hotel was OK. The room itself was nice and big, but the bathroom did not live up to the 4-star rating. The vanities were in poor shape; missing tile grout was replaced with caulking. The service was good. The Boston Bar had excellent cheese burgers for a reasonable price. The hotel has access to a private beach for a fee of 50 Dirhams. Wish there was WiFi coverage in the room, but it was only in the lobby. The hotel has a swimming pool which we didn't use.	
Sep 28 2007 	good hotel near to good restaurants	This hotel is lovely. The receptionists are helpful and all staff smile and greet guests as and when they see them. The rooms were really spacious although the bathrooms were a little disappointing in design but the main thing is that everything was clean! my sis and I shared a room and had a tiny problem in that the AC seemed to be set to 15 degrees whenever we left the room so we would be cold for at least half an hour while we waited for the room to heat up which was bizaare considering it was 45 degrees outside. my mum's room did not have that problem so we must have had a dodgy ac. The rooftop pool although bit small was perfect temp and also never got too crowded. was perfect way to relax after long days of sightseeing and before dinner as the pool would stay open til 10pm.its a good place to stay for those on a budget as there is a street full of restaurants just a 2 min walk away where you could have a feast for about £10 per person. We did all the main sights in dubai and travelled everywhere by taxis which are air conditioned so we werent affected by the severe heat outside as most of the things to do in dubai is indoors. the malls are great - must do in dubai are afternoon tea in the burj, wild wadi park and mall of emirates including ski dubai. for a bit of culture go to old dubai which includes the gold souk and have a ride on the water taxis as they were great!Overall to do the above be prepared to spend money but its totally worth it!ooh and dont forget to save some money to spend in dubai duty free as its has loads of stuff at good prices!	
Aug 20 2007	Highly Recommend	I agree with the other reviews. Probably the best deal in Dubai if you want to be close to the city and the airport. Taxi fare is very reasonable from here.It's very attractive, the staff is very attentive (they sent a cake for my daughter's birthday) and the rooms are nice and comfortable. The FIVE restaurant has a great assortment for breakfast and omelets cooked to order and a variety of specialty dinners in the evening. The Boston bar also has good food with healthy portions.The bellmen make sure your wait for luggage or a taxi is minutes at the most.The area surrounding the hotel offer just about anything you need as far as dining and everyday conveniences. All within walking distance.If there is any drawback it would be a small pool but those staying here probably aren't interested in that.I highly recommend this hotel. I will be staying here frequently.	
Aug 2 2007 	great hotel	We have just returned form Dubai where we spent five days in the Jumeirah Rotana Hotel. The Staff here were very friendly and helpful- they wrote my name for me in Arabic which I used to get inscripted on a silver chain. The porters were always on hand to call a taxi -we waited no more than two minutes for one. The rooms were lovely and spacious and always very clean. Even though there was a bar on the premises we never heard any noise from our room, we found the area to be very quiet all the time. The hotel pool was on the rooftop, we only went there once or twice and there was never many people there. We went to the Jumeirah Beach Park for sunbathing as it was only 15 dirham in the taxi and 5 dirham per person entrance fee. If you wanted a sun lounger, which you would as the sand is very hot it cost 15 dirham each. You can go to a private beach at the Dubai Marina beach hotel and spa which was lovely however, it cost 100 dirham each as well as fifteen in the taxi. Don't use the hotel phone it cost us 110 dirham to make a four minute phone call to our parents in Bulgaria. We really enjoyed Dubai, the architecture is amazing. The hotels are out of this world especially &quot;The One And Only Royal Mirage&quot; and the &quot;Mina A Salam&quot;. These are very Arabian in design and nicer than the Burj Al Arab in my opinion. There are a lot of shopping malls. The better ones are the mall of the emirates and the Madinat Jumeirah which has lots of restaurants. It's great the way our hotel had air conditioning as did everywhere in Dubai this time of year.	
