May 18 2007 	Very Pleasant Stay	I booked my stay at the Rotana using Asiarooms.com. I stayed here 9 nights with my wife. Most of the reviews will confirm my experience at this Hotel. Although not 5 star it more than lives up to a 4 star rating with large spacious rooms, kept very clean with all the facilities you can expect. The location was very good more or less within a stone's throw of all the main attractions in Dubai (taxis are relatively inexpensive). The staff were in particular very pleasant and courteous. Breakfast was great. The gym was fully equipped with modern equipment though was not surprisingly empty most of the time. The pool on the top floor was a great plus, albeit on the small side, it was sufficient to burn some calories consumed the previous night and then chill out on the deck chairs. The only negative was that the AC in my room was slightly noisey, but then again it didn't stop me from sleeping.All in all a great stay and I would come here again.	
